a("Battle of Dien Bien Phu","1954-03-13","1954-05-07","Vietnam",["Battle","Colonial War"],"Dien Bien Phu in 1954 was the climactic First Indochina War battle. Viet Minh under Giap besieged the French garrison. The French defeat led to the Geneva Accords, ending colonial rule—one of the 20th century's most significant anticolonial victories.",[["1953-11","French establish base"],["1954-03-13","Artillery bombardment"],["1954-04","Airstrip unusable"],["1954-05-07","Garrison surrenders"],["1954-07","Geneva Accords"],["1954","Vietnam divided"]]);
a("Tet Offensive","1968-01-30","1968-03-28","Vietnam",["Battle","Vietnam War"],"The Tet Offensive of 1968 was a massive surprise attack during Vietnamese New Year. Though a military failure, it was a psychological victory that shattered American public confidence and turned the war's course.",[["1968-01-30","Coordinated attacks"],["1968-01-31","US Embassy breached"],["1968-02","Battle of Hue"],["1968-02","Cronkite: 'stalemate'"],["1968-03-31","LBJ won't run again"],["1968-05","Paris talks begin"]]);
a("Battle of Ia Drang","1965-11-14","1965-11-18","Vietnam",["Battle","Vietnam War"],"The Battle of Ia Drang in 1965 was the first major US-North Vietnamese engagement. At Landing Zones X-Ray and Albany, both sides proved their fighting ability. The battle convinced each they could win, escalating the war.",[["1965-11-14","Troops land at LZ X-Ray"],["1965-11-15","'Broken Arrow' called"],["1965-11-16","PAVN withdraw from X-Ray"],["1965-11-17","Ambush at LZ Albany"],["1965-11-18","305 Americans killed"],["1965","War escalates"]]);

