a("Battle of Isandlwana","1879-01-22","1879-01-22","South Africa",["Battle","Colonial War"],"Isandlwana in 1879 was one of the worst British defeats against an indigenous force. 20,000 Zulu warriors overwhelmed 1,800 British troops. The disaster shocked Victorian Britain.",[["1879-01-11","British invade Zululand"],["1879-01-22","Chelmsford divides force"],["1879-01-22","Zulu impis attack"],["1879-01-22","1,300+ killed"],["1879-01-22","Rorke's Drift follows"],["1879-07","Zulu kingdom defeated"]]);
a("Battle of Adwa","1896-03-01","1896-03-01","Ethiopia",["Battle","Colonial War"],"The Battle of Adwa in 1896 was Ethiopia's decisive victory over Italian invaders. Menelik II's 100,000 defeated 17,700 Italians, preserving Ethiopia as Africa's only uncolonized nation. It became a powerful symbol of African resistance.",[["1895","Italy invades"],["1896-02","Menelik mobilizes"],["1896-03-01","Italians attack"],["1896-03-01","Ethiopians overwhelm enemy"],["1896-03-01","6,000+ Italians killed"],["1896-10","Sovereignty recognized"]]);
a("Battle of Tsushima","1905-05-27","1905-05-28","Japan",["Battle","Naval Battle"],"Tsushima in 1905 was the Russo-Japanese War's decisive naval battle. Admiral Togo annihilated the Russian Baltic Fleet that had sailed 18,000 miles. Japan sank 21 ships while losing only 3 torpedo boats, establishing Japan as a world power.",[["1904-10","Baltic Fleet departs"],["1905-05","Fleet arrives"],["1905-05-27","Togo intercepts"],["1905-05-27","Crosses the T"],["1905-05-28","21 ships sunk or captured"],["1905-09","Treaty of Portsmouth"]]);
a("Siege of Port Arthur","1904-08-01","1905-01-02","China",["Siege","Russo-Japanese War"],"The Siege of Port Arthur from 1904-1905 was the Russo-Japanese War's longest engagement. Japan suffered 57,000+ casualties taking the Russian naval base. 203 Meter Hill's capture allowed artillery to sink the Russian fleet.",[["1904-08","Siege begins"],["1904-08","First assault fails"],["1904-11","203 Meter Hill captured"],["1904-12","Fleet sunk in harbor"],["1905-01-02","Garrison surrenders"],["1905","Treaty of Portsmouth"]]);
a("Siege of Khartoum","1884-03-13","1885-01-26","Sudan",["Siege","Colonial War"],"The Siege of Khartoum from 1884-1885 saw General Gordon besieged by Mahdist forces. A relief expedition arrived two days too late—Gordon was killed on the palace steps. The fall shocked Victorian Britain.",[["1881","Mahdist revolt begins"],["1884-03","Gordon arrives in Khartoum"],["1884","Mahdists surround city"],["1884","Government delays rescue"],["1885-01-26","City falls; Gordon killed"],["1885-01-28","Relief arrives too late"]]);
a("Battle of Manila Bay","1898-05-01","1898-05-01","Philippines",["Battle","Naval Battle"],"The Battle of Manila Bay in 1898 was a decisive American victory in the Spanish-American War. Dewey destroyed the entire Spanish fleet without losing an American life, marking US emergence as a Pacific power.",[["1898-04","Spanish-American War begins"],["1898-05-01","American fleet enters Manila Bay"],["1898-05-01","'Fire when ready, Gridley'"],["1898-05-01","Spanish fleet destroyed"],["1898-05-01","Zero American deaths"],["1898","US acquires Philippines"]]);
a("Battle of Balaclava","1854-10-25","1854-10-25","Crimea",["Battle","Crimean War"],"The Battle of Balaclava in 1854 is known for the Charge of the Light Brigade. Miscommunicated orders sent 670 cavalry into Russian guns. Immortalized by Tennyson, it symbolizes both military valor and blind obedience's futility.",[["1854-10-25","Russians attack supply base"],["1854-10-25","Thin Red Line repulses cavalry"],["1854-10-25","Heavy Brigade succeeds"],["1854-10-25","Light Brigade charges guns"],["1854-10-25","118 killed, 127 wounded"],["1854","Tennyson writes poem"]]);

