a("Korean War","1950-06-25","1953-07-27","Korea",["War","Cold War"],"The Korean War (1950-1953) began with North Korea's invasion and drew in UN forces and China. 2.5 million killed, ending in armistice near the original border. No peace treaty has been signed.",[["1950-06-25","North Korea invades"],["1950-09-15","Inchon landing"],["1950-11","Chinese intervention"],["1951-07","Armistice talks begin"],["1953-07-27","Armistice signed"],["1953","Peninsula divided"]]);
a("Vietnam War","1955-11-01","1975-04-30","Vietnam",["War","Cold War"],"The Vietnam War (1955-1975) killed 2-3 million Vietnamese and 58,000 Americans. US military involvement peaked at 500,000+ troops. The fall of Saigon in 1975 unified Vietnam under communist rule.",[["1964","Gulf of Tonkin; escalation"],["1965","Combat troops arrive"],["1968","Tet Offensive"],["1973","Paris Peace Accords"],["1975-04-30","Fall of Saigon"],["1975","Vietnam reunified"]]);
a("Falklands War","1982-04-02","1982-06-14","South Atlantic",["War","Modern War"],"The Falklands War was a 1982 ten-week conflict between Argentina and Britain. Britain dispatched a task force 8,000 miles and recaptured the islands. The war boosted Thatcher and toppled Argentina's junta.",[["1982-04-02","Argentina invades"],["1982-05-02","Belgrano sunk"],["1982-05-04","Sheffield hit"],["1982-05-21","British land at San Carlos"],["1982-06-14","Argentine surrender"],["1982","Junta falls"]]);
a("Gulf War 1991","1991-01-17","1991-02-28","Middle East",["War","Modern War"],"The Gulf War (1991) liberated Kuwait from Iraqi occupation. A 39-day air campaign and 100-hour ground war demonstrated precision weapons and established US post-Cold War military dominance.",[["1990-08-02","Iraq invades Kuwait"],["1991-01-17","Air campaign begins"],["1991-02-24","Ground war begins"],["1991-02-27","Kuwait liberated"],["1991-02-28","Ceasefire"],["1991","US dominance established"]]);
a("Spanish Civil War","1936-07-17","1939-04-01","Spain",["War","Modern War"],"The Spanish Civil War (1936-1939) pitted Republicans against Franco's Nationalists with intervention from Nazi Germany, Italy, and the USSR. Guernica's bombing symbolized modern warfare's brutality. Franco's dictatorship lasted until 1975.",[["1936-07-17","Military uprising"],["1937-04-26","Bombing of Guernica"],["1937","International Brigades"],["1938","Battle of the Ebro"],["1939-04-01","Franco declares victory"],["1975","Franco dies"]]);
a("Second Sino-Japanese War","1937-07-07","1945-09-02","East Asia",["War","World War II"],"The Second Sino-Japanese War (1937-1945) killed 15-20 million Chinese civilians. Beginning with the Marco Polo Bridge Incident and including the Nanjing Massacre, it merged with WWII's Pacific Theater.",[["1937-07-07","Marco Polo Bridge Incident"],["1937-12","Nanjing Massacre"],["1938","Chinese retreat to Chongqing"],["1941-12","Merges with Pacific Theater"],["1944","Operation Ichi-Go"],["1945-09-02","Japan surrenders"]]);
a("Soviet-Afghan War","1979-12-24","1989-02-15","Afghanistan",["War","Cold War"],"The Soviet-Afghan War (1979-1989) was the Soviet Union's 'Vietnam.' Mujahideen backed by the US and Pakistan fought Soviet forces. US-supplied Stinger missiles negated Soviet air superiority. The withdrawal contributed to the USSR's fall.",[["1979-12-24","Soviets invade"],["1980","Mujahideen resistance"],["1984","CIA provides billions"],["1986","Stinger missiles"],["1988","Geneva Accords"],["1989-02-15","Soviets leave"]]);
a("Taiping Rebellion","1850-12-01","1864-08-01","China",["War","Rebellion"],"The Taiping Rebellion (1850-1864) killed 20-30 million, making it one of history's deadliest conflicts. Led by Hong Xiuquan who claimed to be Jesus's brother, it controlled much of southern China before suppression.",[["1850","Hong proclaims kingdom"],["1853","Nanjing captured"],["1860","Western-trained armies enlisted"],["1864","Nanjing falls; Hong dies"],["1864","20-30 million dead"],["1864","Qing fatally weakened"]]);
a("American Civil War","1861-04-12","1865-04-09","United States",["War","Modern War"],"The American Civil War (1861-1865) killed 620,000-750,000. The Union preserved the nation and abolished slavery through the 13th Amendment, fundamentally transforming American society.",[["1861-04-12","Fort Sumter"],["1862","Emancipation Proclamation"],["1863","Gettysburg; Vicksburg"],["1864","Sherman's March"],["1865-04-09","Lee surrenders"],["1865-04-14","Lincoln assassinated"]]);
a("World War I","1914-07-28","1918-11-11","Global",["War","World War"],"World War I (1914-1918) killed 17 million. Triggered by Archduke Franz Ferdinand's assassination, it featured devastating trench warfare. Four empires collapsed. It set the stage for World War II.",[["1914-06-28","Archduke assassinated"],["1914-09","Trench warfare begins"],["1916","Verdun; Somme"],["1917","Russia Revolution; US enters"],["1918","German offensive fails"],["1918-11-11","Armistice"]]);
a("World War II","1939-09-01","1945-09-02","Global",["War","World War"],"World War II (1939-1945) killed 70-85 million. The Allies defeated the Axis across global theaters. The Holocaust killed 6 million Jews. It led to the UN, Cold War, and atomic age.",[["1939-09-01","Germany invades Poland"],["1940","Fall of France"],["1941","Barbarossa; Pearl Harbor"],["1943","Stalingrad; Midway"],["1944-06-06","D-Day"],["1945-09-02","Japan surrenders"]]);
a("War of 1812","1812-06-18","1815-02-17","North America",["War","Modern War"],"The War of 1812 between the US and Britain saw Washington D.C. burned and the Star-Spangled Banner written. The Treaty of Ghent restored the status quo but cemented American national identity.",[["1812-06-18","US declares war"],["1814-08-24","British burn Washington"],["1814-09","Battle of Baltimore"],["1814-12-24","Treaty of Ghent"],["1815-01-08","Battle of New Orleans"],["1815","American identity cemented"]]);
a("Crimean War","1853-10-16","1856-03-30","Europe",["War","Modern War"],"The Crimean War (1853-1856) featured the Charge of the Light Brigade and Florence Nightingale's nursing reforms. It was the first war covered extensively by media and photography.",[["1854-03","France and Britain join"],["1854-10","Charge of Light Brigade"],["1854-11","Nightingale arrives"],["1855-09","Sevastopol captured"],["1856-03","Treaty of Paris"],["1856","Russia begins reforms"]]);
