a("Iran-Iraq War","1980-09-22","1988-08-20","Middle East",["War","Modern War"],"The Iran-Iraq War (1980-1988) killed 500,000-1 million in a brutal stalemate featuring trench warfare, human wave attacks, and chemical weapons. It ended without significant territorial changes.",[["1980-09-22","Iraq invades Iran"],["1982","Iran invades Iraq; stalemate"],["1983","Chemical weapons used"],["1987","US reflagging tankers"],["1988-08-20","Ceasefire"],["1988","Both nations devastated"]]);
a("Six-Day War","1967-06-05","1967-06-10","Middle East",["War","Modern War"],"The Six-Day War in 1967 saw Israel preemptively destroy the Egyptian air force, then conquer the Sinai, West Bank, Gaza, and Golan Heights. The war tripled Israeli territory and created the Palestinian occupation issue.",[["1967-06-05","Preemptive strikes"],["1967-06-05","Egyptian air force destroyed"],["1967-06-07","Jerusalem captured"],["1967-06-08","Sinai conquered"],["1967-06-10","Golan taken"],["1967","UN Resolution 242"]]);
a("Yom Kippur War","1973-10-06","1973-10-25","Middle East",["War","Modern War"],"The Yom Kippur War in 1973 saw Egypt and Syria surprise-attack Israel. Israeli counterattacks prevailed, but the war triggered the oil crisis and led to the Camp David Accords.",[["1973-10-06","Egypt and Syria attack"],["1973-10-06","Egypt crosses Suez"],["1973-10-15","Israel crosses Suez"],["1973-10-17","OPEC embargo"],["1973-10-25","Ceasefire"],["1978","Camp David Accords"]]);
a("Peloponnesian War","0431-01-01","0404-01-01","Greece",["War","Ancient War"],"The Peloponnesian War (431-404 BC) between Athens and Sparta devastated Greece. Athens suffered plague, the Sicilian disaster, and final defeat. The war ended the Golden Age and left Greece weakened for Macedonian conquest.",[["431 BC","War begins"],["430 BC","Plague; Pericles dies"],["415 BC","Sicilian Expedition"],["413 BC","Sicilian disaster"],["405 BC","Fleet destroyed"],["404 BC","Athens surrenders"]]);
